<hl>
<seg id=1> The Irish Republican Army declared a cease-fire. </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> Xinhua News Agency, London, 31 August, by Li Wenhao The Irish Republican Army declared that from this midnight on, the organization would stop every military movement and cease fire "without preconditions and of indefinite duration". </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=3> In a statement to the news of England and Ireland, the Irish Republican Army said that with consideration to the current situation and improvement of the peace process of Ireland, the organization made the above decision and notified all its subordinate troops. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> The statement asked the English government to face its responsibilities, urge all parties to meet the new situation firmly and patiently after the cease-fire, negotiate with the Irish government and all the major parties of Northern Ireland to solve the conflict of Northern Ireland ultimately. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=5> According to the statement, the cease-fire of the Irish Republican Army provided the chance to solve the problem of Northern Ireland "fairly and ultimately". </seg>
<seg id=6> However, the Irish Republican Army reiterated that it would still stick to "the republican target", that is, the united Ireland. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=7> In order to unify Northern Ireland and the Republic of Ireland, the Irish Republican Army had been involved with the violence in Northern Ireland for 25 years. </seg>
</p>
